This paper is likely to belong to the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with the skip-gram embedding of words and their semantic and syntactic roles. It could also be categorized under Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it involves the use of embeddings and subvectors. Additionally, it could fall under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with natural language processing and understanding. Neural Networks (cs.NE) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) could also be possible categories as they involve the use of embeddings and subvectors in these fields.
